title: TV highlights: Twins compete for $222,222.22 in prize money on “Twinning”
text:
A few "Twinning" contestants on challenge day. (Courtesy of VH1) By — Lauren McEwen July 21 at 6:18 PM (All times Eastern.)
“Starring Adam West” (Showtime at 7 p.m.) recounts the life and career of the 85-year-old actor and the campaign by his fans to get him a star on the Hollywood Walk of Fame.
Pulitzer Prize-winning journalist and activist Jose Antonio Vargas’s new documentary, “White People” (MTV at 8), examines race in America by asking young white people to be upfront about race, whiteness and privilege.
SERIES PREMIERE: The three-week miniseries “Life on the Reef” (PBS at 8) gives an in-depth look at Australia’s Great Barrier Reef.
The remaining 10 home chefs make steaks for more than 100 ranchers and cowboys on “MasterChef” (Fox at 8).
On “Extant” (CBS at 9), Molly makes a shocking discovery while attempting to develop a virus to wipe out alien hybrids.
RETURNING SHOW: “Dating Naked: Playing for Keeps” (VH1 at 9) returns for Season 2. In the premiere, the main two daters, Kerri and Chris, arrive in the Philippines, shedding their clothes and opening themselves up to the possibility of romance.
RETURNING SHOW: “Last Comic Standing” (NBC at 9) returns for Season 9, featuring judges Keenen Ivory Wayans, Roseanne Barr and Norm Macdonald.
Shark-filled twisters hit Washington in “Sharknado 3: Oh Hell No” (Syfy at 9), the latest installment in the offbeat monster-movie franchise.
SERIES PREMIERE: Nine couples renovate decrepit houses in hopes of winning their dream home in “Home Free” (Fox at 9).
On “I Am Jazz” (TLC at 10), Jazz is apprehensive when her friends suggest a trip to the bowling alley with a group of boys.
Fsociety goes after the most secure data facility in the United States on “Mr. Robot” (USA at 10).
SERIES PREMIERE: Twelve sets of twins compete for $222,222.22 of prize money on “Twinning” (VH1 at 10), a new competition series that asks the contestants to put their “twintuition” to the test.
On “Lachey’s Bar” (A&E at 10:30), Drew and Nick head to a nearby brewery to find beers to add to their selection.
“Southpaw” actor Jake Gyllenhaal stops by “The Daily Show With Jon Stewart” (Comedy Central at 11).
“Vacation” actor Ed Helms and “Trainwreck” star Brie Larson visit “Jimmy Kimmel Live” (ABC at 11:30) with musical guest Joss Stone.
Comedian and “Last Comic Standing” judge Norm Macdonald is on “The Tonight Show Starring Jimmy Fallon” (NBC at 11:30) with actress JoAnna Garcia Swisher and musical guests Flo Rida and Jeremih.
— Lauren McEwen
